{{ja-kanjitab|ほう|yomi=o}}
From {{der|ja|ltc|-|sort=ほう}} {{ltc-l|法}}. Originally, the [[漢音#Japanese|''kan'on'']] was {{m|ja|はふ|tr=fafu}}, and the [[呉音#Japanese|''goon'']] was {{m|ja|ほふ|tr=fofu}}, although both became {{m|ja|ほう|tr=hō}} in modern Japanese. It is suggested that the ''kan'on'' was used in the general senses, while the ''goon'' was used in Buddhist contexts.
